Red Gold is an American apple variety. It was developed in Cashmere, Washington and introduced in 1946.

*Father of Amrut Mitti passes away.*. Deepak Suchde, had started his social work in Shardagram, a Nai Talim institute in Saurashtra on Gandhian principles since around 1980. He had good experience in rural industries like soap making, oil mills etc. He had diverted his focus from rural industry to agroecology after reading series of articles on ill-effects of chemical farming written by Kapil Shah around 1996 in Gujarati. He found that working for Sajiv Kheti is more need of an hour at that time.. He was a born experimenter, had learnt a lot from his guru, Natueco Farming  fame Dr. Sheepad A. Dabholkar of Prayog Pariwar with great passion. He experimented and improved Dabholkar's techniques at various places in Maharashtra  including at well-known Yusuf Meharali Centre near Mumbai.. He was a passionate promoter of organic farming, which he named as Amrut krushi later on. Since more than decade he was based at his farm owned by Malpani Trust in Bajwada on the bank of river Narmada near Indore in MP.. He presented his experimental results with scientific ground at national and international fora. He has innovated the concepts of Amrut mitti, Amrutpani and training of root systems, which was his unique technological contribution to the organic movement. Not only farmers, plenty of scientists and bureaucrats in formal system were inspired and trained by him. He has influenced the main stream agricultural system like ICAR.. Very recently he conducted a training workshop on 23-24th Oct., 2019 in North Gujarat and was to visit Punjab from 7th Nov., onwards.. He was not only a missionary for chemical free sustainable farming, but also a spiritual traveller.. He passed away, while he was travelling in a  train near Itarasi in MP at around 6 pm.
